This paper deals with data mining techniques for predicting student performance, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). It also involves analyzing factors that affect student performance, which can be related to educational data mining (cs.ED) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of classification techniques such as Naive Bayes and J48, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational engineering (cs.CE).
